<p xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><italic toggle="yes">S<sub>i</sub></italic> and <italic toggle="yes">U<sub>i</sub></italic> are the spatially structured and unstructured effects utilized in the Besag, York, Molli&#233; (BYM) model [<xref rid="B40-ijerph-19-12314" ref-type="bibr">40</xref>]. In this study the parameterization of the BYM model proposed by Simpson at al. which assigns penalized complexity (PC) priors is used [<xref rid="B41-ijerph-19-12314" ref-type="bibr">41</xref>]. Typically referred to as the &#8220;BYM2&#8221; model, it utilizes scaled spatially structured and unstructured components (<inline-formula><mml:math id="mm5" overflow="scroll"><mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>S</mml:mi><mml:mo>*</mml:mo></mml:msub><mml:mo>&#160;</mml:mo><mml:mi>and</mml:mi><mml:mo>&#160;</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>U</mml:mi><mml:mo>*</mml:mo></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:mrow></mml:math></inline-formula>) and is defined as:<disp-formula id="FD6-ijerph-19-12314"><mml:math id="mm6" display="block" overflow="scroll"><mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>&#952;</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>d</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mi>&#946;</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mrow><mml:msqrt><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>&#964;</mml:mi><mml:mi>b</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:msqrt></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac><mml:mfenced><mml:mrow><mml:msqrt><mml:mrow><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo>&#8722;</mml:mo><mml:mi>&#966;</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msqrt><mml:mo>&#160;</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>S</mml:mi><mml:mo>*</mml:mo></mml:msub><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msqrt><mml:mi>&#966;</mml:mi></mml:msqrt><mml:msub><mml:mi>U</mml:mi><mml:mo>*</mml:mo></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:mrow></mml:mrow></mml:math></disp-formula></p>